      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STEELY ZAC (9) comes to the city having placed in his two Penrith outings so far. Cops a wide draw but did show gate speed last start so may have enough pace to push forward. Looks close to a win as does MCWEAPON (3) who has placed in three of four starts so far this campaign, leading from this draw and fighting well to go under by a head when second last start at Newcastle. Big chance. TINY PRANCER (6) finished second on debut despite breaking, beaten less than 6 metres at Newcastle. Placed in a trial here since. Should have learned from the experience so could go one better. WARRAWEE WAY BACK (1) is stepping out for the first time. By Warrawee Needy and hails from the Simon Bigeni Jnr stable. Trialling well and should have no excuses from this advantageous draw so keep safe.",
